President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 20 to May 26, 2012, as Emergency Medical Services Week. The proclamation recognizes the essential contributions of emergency medical services (EMS) personnel to public safety and public health. It honors the men and women who serve as EMS practitioners, including first responders, emergency medical technicians, paramedics, 911 dispatchers, firefighters, law enforcement officers, and professionals in the healthcare system. The proclamation highlights the dedication and commitment of EMS personnel to saving lives and calls for support and services to strengthen the EMS system and improve preparedness in homes and hospitals across America. President Obama encourages all Americans to observe this occasion by showing support for their local EMS providers and taking steps to enhance personal safety and preparedness.